Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Milesian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine, micaceous, buff-brown. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Parallels from Miletus are published by G. Joehrens. 'Amphorenstempel aus den Grabungen in Milet 1899-2007', Arch.Anz. 2009, 213. Probably same die as 1925,0119.105; it is probable that one of these pieces was drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.51,10, with I not H at the end). Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0069)
